definition: Ye Xuanping (1924-), former Governor of Guangdong 廣東|广东[Guang3 dong1]
flat/level/equal/to tie (make the same score)/to draw (score)/calm/peaceful/see also 平聲|平声[ping2 sheng1]

sentences.english: President Mr. YE Xuanping is enjoying the painting from Mr. GUAN Wei.
sentences.chinese: 會長葉選平在興致勃勃地欣賞關偉的作品。

sentences.english: Hundred-year's Histroy of Guangzhou has reminded Mr. Ye Xuanping of a lot of anecdotes in his childhood.
sentences.chinese: 《廣州百年風情》令葉選平會長回憶起不少童年趣事。
